What is programming language?
A. Programming language is a set of rules in sending instructions to a machine to perform specific tasks.


What jdk contains or composed of and define each components?
A. JDK contains JRE (Java Runtime Environment), JVM (Java Virtual Machine), an archiver (jar), a compiler (javac), 
	a documentation generator (javadoc), and an interpreter/loader.


