what is class?
A. Class is a blueprint for an object in Java.


What is object?
A. An object is the instance of a class.


What is the entry point of an application?
A. The main method is the entry point of an application.


Why is main static?
A. The main is static so that the compiler can call the main method without having to create an object.


Which class is the superclass of all classes?
A. The Object class is the superclass of all classes.


What is the difference between path and classpath variables?
