What is the difference between an Interface and Abstract class?
A. Classes use Abstract class by using the keyword "extends", whereas an interface is used by using the keyword "implements".
	While there are no default constructors in either, the interface methods are public by default, and interface variables are final.
	An abstract class's internal memory is faster.


Can you make an Object from an Interface and Abstract class ? if not how do you use it?
A. You cannot create an object of an interface OR an abstract class. 
	We can use an interface by implementing it to a class and instantiating that class,
	and by inheriting from the abstract class and overriding its abstract methods. This allows us to instantiate the subclass. 


what is Access Specifier?
A. Access specifier/modifier is a java entity that helps us to restrict the scope of a package, class, constructor, method, variable,
	or other data. They are public, private, protected, and default.


What is OOP ? Define each feature of java OOP.
A. OOP stands for Object Oriented Programming. The features of OOPs are Polymorphism, Abstraction, Inheritance, , and Encapsulation.
	Polymorphism is used for method hiding. This includes method overloading and method overriding.
	Method overloading is when we have the same method name as the parent class, but we pass different parameters to make it an entirely different method.
	Method overriding is when we have the same method name and same method parameters as the parent class, but a different body. 
	We have to use the @override annotation for the child class method in method override.
	Abstraction is used for implementation hiding. 
	-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------


What is Java Package and which package is imported by default?
A. A Java package is used to group related classes together into a folder for easier access and efficiency. 
	The java.lang package is internally imported by default into every class.


What is API? Name list of API that you have used so far.
A. ------------------------------------------------------


Does java support multiple inheritance, explain why or why not?
A. Java does not support multiple inheritance because if both parent classes contain methods with the same signature,
	the compiler won't know which method is called upon. 


What is method overloading and when it happens?
A. Method overloading is when we use the same method name as a parent class method, but with different parameters. 


Explain exceptions in java and how to handle it.
A. An exception in java is an error existing in the code of an application. This can be either a checked/compile time exception,
	or an unchecked/runtime exception. We can handle exceptions by either using the 'throws' keyword, or a try-catch block.


What is static keyword in java? How it has been used in variables and methods ?
A. The static keyword is used in java to make an attribute a part of a class. 
	It can be called using the class name and doesn't require creating an object. 
	Static has been used in variables to keep a class value constant, never allowing it to be reassigned.
	A static method is used to access only other static methods and data. Which allows the method to change even a static value.


What is final and how it has been used variables and methods?
A. final is a keyword in Java that does not allow any further reassignment or overriding of a variable or method once used. 
	A final variable is used to keep a constant value, which is a part of the class. 
	A final method can only call/use other final methods or variables. This allows a final variable's manipulation.

What is final, finally and finalize?
A. final is a keyword in java that finalizes a method or variable value from being reassigned or overriden once the keyword is used.
	finally is a keyword used during exception handling at the end of the try and catch block. 
	Regardless of the try or catch block successfully executing, the finally block will always execute. 
	finalize is a method that the garbage collector always calls before deletion/destroy


What is a constructor ?
A. A constructor is a block of code similar to a method. It's initialized during object creation. 


Can we have multiple constructors in a class?
A. Yes, we can have multiple constructors in a class. This can be achieved when the constructors assign the class fields in different ways.


If we don't have a constructor declared, what is called during the object creation?
A. When we don't have a constructor declared, the default constructor is called during object creation.


