Difference between while and do..while loop?
A. The difference between the while loop and the do-while is that the do-while will always loop at least once no matter what. 
	If the conditions of a while loop are not met, there is a chance for the while loop to never run. 
	But because the do-while loop has its 'do' code block first, before its condition within the while block, this loop will always run at least once.


