what is multithreading in java?
A. Multithreading in java is when you can execute multiple threads within a file. 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What is the use of synchronization in Java?
A. The use of synchronization in Java is to protect a method against errors that may come up in multithreading. 
	Synchronization allows only one thread at a time to enter and execute a method. 
	This way another thread won't enter a method at the same time as one thread, and manipulate the values before the first thread is complete.

